      "rationale": "The C++ finite-volume solver (v4.2.1) and Python hemolysis post-processor (v1.8.3) are maintained in a Git repository with CI/CD build verification tests. Unit tests cover 94% of solver utility functions. However, software fault modes specific to the COU — including race conditions in parallel hemolysis accumulation, numerical instability at high-shear edge cases, and floating-point exception handling — are not covered by the existing test suite and were not exercised during validation."
