    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. CFD predictions of NIH agree with bench measurements within 20% across all 5 operating points; RH < 1 at worst-case conditions satisfies the regulatory acceptance criterion. The software quality assurance factor is met at Gradation 2 based on version control and build verification coverage. The assessment team notes that the solver pipeline was exercised only under nominal completion conditions; no software fault injection or numerical edge-case testing was performed. This gap is considered acceptable within the MRL 2 scope given that bench testing provides independent confirmation of model outputs.",
